.TH "batadv_mcast_mla_br_addr_cpy" 9 "batadv_mcast_mla_br_addr_cpy" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_mcast_mla_br_addr_cpy \- copy a bridge multicast address
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" batadv_mcast_mla_br_addr_cpy
.BI "(char *dst "  ","
.BI "const struct br_ip *src "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dst" 12
destination to write to - a multicast MAC address
.IP "src" 12
source to read from - a multicast IP address
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Converts a given multicast IPv4/IPv6 address from a bridge
to its matching multicast MAC address and copies it into the given
destination buffer.

Caller needs to make sure the destination buffer can hold
at least ETH_ALEN bytes.
